cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.SI 

This paper discusses relation extraction from text, which is a common task in natural language processing (NLP). The use of crowdsourcing and machine learning also suggests a focus on NLP. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper discusses data quality and the use of metrics, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of knowledge-bases and relation classification could also fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper discusses enhancing training data, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
